[SN]TITLE[SN]
West Malling farmer fears loss of migrant workers will harm business

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A farmer in the South East has spoken of his fear the decision to leave the EU will damage his business which relies on seasonal workers from Europe.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
26 June 2016 Last updated at 17:23 BST
Leave campaigners have promoted a points-based immigration system.
But the National Farmers' Union in Kent is concerned a lack of migrant workers will push costs up and more food will have to be imported.
The BBC's Charlie Rose reports.
